      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DESANTO (7) was a heavily backed $1.80 favourite when resuming last start in a similar maiden to this but was edged out on the line after looking the winner for much of the straight. Lightly raced filly who should make significant progress following that run. Drawn to advantage so she looks a huge chance to go one better. GRAM (1) has transferred from Anthony and Sam Freedman to Tony Gollan and returns from a 21-week spell. Last appeared when in the money over this distance at the Caulfield Heath. Sparingly raced four-year-old who looks ready to fire following a comfortable recent trial win. ZOUSTROLOGY (4) is up in class today but made a nice return at the Sunshine Coast last start. Cannot be ruled out from the nice draw. SWORD OF LEGACY (10) is first-up from a 21-week spell and has switched from Waller to Matt Dunn. Went close at Group 3 level as a juvenile. Market watch. MAGIC INVADER (3) is going well in easier races and can sneak into the frame without surprising.",
